// PX4 Renode platform — STM32H743-based, modelled on Pixhawk FMU-v6X.
//
// The CPU/NVIC/MPU/USARTs/RAM/flash all live in Renode's stock
// `stm32h743.repl` already; we just `using` it. Per-test attachment
// of USART2 to a host pty is done at run-time by the companion
// `.resc` script — that's a connector binding, not a platform
// description.
//
// This file is intentionally a thin extension point. Add overrides
// only when a particular phase-13 test needs a peripheral the stock
// platform doesn't model — for example, a fake sensor on SPI to
// drive `gyro_watch`'s spike detection. Until then, the upstream
// description is exactly what we want.

using "platforms/cpus/stm32h743.repl"
